{"type":"message","id":"423b8e39","parentId":"dc754377","timestamp":"2026-03-26T02:40:44.539Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The summary JSON already correctly shows:\n- `signal_stale: True`\n- `signal_stale_reason: \"信号已过期：预测文件最新日期 2026-03-03，但特征数据已到 2026-03-10，落后 7 天\"`\n- `execution_status: signal_stale_hold`\n\nSo the detection IS working. The issue is that:\n1. The script's print output during cron runs is going to logs, not visible to the user\n2. The dashboard HTML shows a stale banner only when `signal_stale` is True (which it is), but it might not be prominent enough\n\n\n3. The markdown reports should clearly indicate when trading is halted\n\nNow I need to make the fixes more explicit. The stale detection is already in place, but I should add the current date comparison in the `load_latest_signals()` function to make the staleness even clearer. The real issue is that the script runs silently through cron, so the stale banner in the dashboard HTML might not be getting rendered properly or isn't visible enough to alert the user.\n\nLet me check the actual generated dashboard to see if the banner is appearing correctly, and then I'll focus on enhancing the markdown report and console output to make the stale status unmistakable.\n\nFor the fixes, I need to update the stale detection to compare against both the feature date and the current date, add a clear banner in the markdown report when signals are stale, and ensure the dashboard banner renders properly with a note about refreshing live signals.","thinkingSignature":"97409b581ee8f181cbd286d970d28ffaa777dd520f66bab91b7964b78cf600e6"},{"type":"text","text":"检测已正常工作（`signal_stale=True`，`signal_stale_hold`）。问题在于：报告/面板对过期状态的展示不够醒目，且没有给出刷新入口。我来修复 `generate_report()` 中的过期展示，增强面板 banner，并补全刷新触发说明。\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_y045b9uxd9q5_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/run_breadth_paper_trading.py","offset":290,"limit":50}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43196,"output":437,"cacheRead":22075,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":65708,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774492832057,"responseId":"0613cfa028626bdf5361f33ae7ded937"}}
{"type":"message","id":"edc10de7","parentId":"423b8e39","timestamp":"2026-03-26T02:40:44.623Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_y045b9uxd9q5_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"    # 买入（等权分配）\n    if target_risk > 0.01 and buy_list:\n        total_asset = state[\"cash\"] + sum(h.get(\"current_value\", h[\"shares\"] * h[\"avg_price\"]) for h in state[\"holdings\"].values())\n        per_stock_value = (total_asset * target_risk) / len(buy_list)\n        for sym in buy_list:\n            price = live_prices.get(sym, {}).get(\"price\", 1.0)\n            if price <= 0:\n                price = 1.0\n            shares = int(per_stock_value / price / 100) * 100\n            if shares > 0 and state[\"cash\"] >= shares * price * 1.002:\n                cost = shares * price * (1 + 0.000885)\n                state[\"cash\"] -= cost\n                state[\"holdings\"][sym] = {\n                    \"shares\": shares,\n                    \"avg_price\": price,\n                    \"current_price\": price,\n                    \"current_value\": shares * price,\n                    \"buy_date\": signals_date,\n                }\n\n    # 更新总资产和净值\n    total_value = state[\"cash\"]\n    for sym, info in state[\"holdings\"].items():\n        total_value += info.get(\"current_value\", info[\"shares\"] * info[\"current_price\"])\n\n    nav = total_value / paper_capital\n    state[\"nav_history\"].append({\n        \"date\": signals_date,\n        \"nav\": round(nav, 4),\n        \"cash\": round(state[\"cash\"], 2),\n    })\n\n    save_state(state, state_file)\n    return state, nav, position_scale, breadth_val, buy_list, sell_list\n\n\ndef refresh_holdings_snapshot(state, live_prices, *, state_file, paper_capital, snapshot_date):\n    holdings = state.get(\"holdings\", {})\n    for sym, info in holdings.items():\n        if sym in live_prices and live_prices[sym].get(\"price\", 0) > 0:\n            info[\"current_price\"] = live_prices[sym][\"price\"]\n            info[\"current_value\"] = info[\"shares\"] * info[\"current_price\"]\n    total_value = state.get(\"cash\", 0.0)\n    for info in holdings.values():\n        total_value += info.get(\"current_value\", info[\"shares\"] * info.get(\"current_price\", info[\"avg_price\"]))\n    nav = total_value / paper_capital if paper_capital > 0 else 1.0\n    state.setdefault(\"nav_history\", []).append({\n        \"date\": snapshot_date,\n        \"nav\": round(nav, 4),\n        \"cash\": round(float(state.get(\"cash\", 0.0)), 2),\n\n[304 more lines in file. Use offset=340 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774492844611}}
